    'Tongji University', 'Philip F. Yuan', 'philipyuan007@tongji.edu.cn', '“Heart of Yong''an” Community Hub',
    'IMPLEMENTED', 'APPROVED',
    0.0, 0.0,
    'SECTION_IV', 'Dali', 'China',
    NULL, NULL,
    'Yong’an Village is surrounded by sinuous mountain landscape with multiple ethnic groups co-existing here. The hub’s aim is to reshape the spiritual dwellings and venue memories of the villagers in the future.', 'The project starts with local architecture typology study. Modern parametric design tool finds its way to encounter traditional building craftsmanship. It inherits and develops local architectural heritage using non-local design approach under a global scope in digital age. Its design novelty should be valued.
In general, the project’s endeavor to encourage ethnic pluralism, community improvement, public welfare, heritage preservation, area conservation, and sustainability should be considered and appreciated by the steering committee.', 'The community center is funded and donated by Tongji University as part of an ongoing social welfare program since 2012. This program is non-profit and equal opportunity, aiming to improve local people’s living conditions building their diverse communities. 
Most construction materials, such as soil, stone, timber, steel are sourced locally, reducing price budget and carbon footprint. 
The project starts with local architecture typology study. Modern parametric design tool finds its way to encounter traditional building craftsmanship. It inherits and develops local architectural heritage using non-local design approach under a global scope in digital age. Its design novelty should be valued.',
