The building aims to be a point of reference for the entire community and its orientation along the east/west axis, as well as allowing it to open onto the panorama of the Gulf of Sant''Eufemia, ensures that the main entrances are easily identifiable from the street.', 'The building houses rooms for meetings and gatherings for the formation and catechism of the Catholic religion which has inclusion and hospitality among its founding values. Hospitality and a sense of community are the principles that guided the design of the building whose shape recalls the archetypal village of houses with sloping roofs and which seeks a formal dialogue with the historic center.',
