    'WM Creative Studio - Relab', 'Wajiha Siddiqui Mehdi', 'wajiha@wmcreativestudio.com.pk', 'Tranquil Abode',
    'IMPLEMENTED', 'APPROVED',
    0.0, 0.0,
    'SECTION_IV', 'Uthal (Balochistan)', 'Pakistan',
    NULL, NULL,
    'Tranquil Abode: A housing prototype located in rugged terrain adjacent to a farm in Uthal, Balochistan, Pakistan, created in response to the devastating floods of 2022.', 'The Tranquil Abode is a culture-specific housing prototype in Uthal, Balochistan, designed in response to the 2022 floods in Pakistan. Its introverted empathetic design prioritizes privacy for women & employs simple construction techniques that can be easily adapted by the community. The prototype utilizes affordable, local materials. Given the catastrophic loss of life during these floods, a double roof has been incorporated to provide temporary refuge in the face of future climate emergencies.', 'GOAL 17 has been achieved through a local NGO''s partnership with the locals & architecture students, which guided the project towards sustainable practices & adaptability benefiting GOAL 13 & 11 by mitigating the impact of climate change. Providing training in neo-vernacular building techniques to the locals, creating jobs & economic growth, satisfies GOAL 8. The participatory design, prioritizing privacy for women & utilizing regional materials, furthers GOAL 10''s aim of reducing inequalities.',
    TRUE,
    'LDP39', 'Muhammad Mehdi, Wajiha Siddiqui Mehdi, Muhamad Nafeel Qureshi, Ilsa Ahmed, Muhammad Bilal, and Nihal Ahmed Barry', NULL, NULL
);

