    'PPD&I -Partnership for Research, Development and Innovation: Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais - UFMG (University), Instituto Federal de Minas Gerais -IFMG (University) and VLI (Enterprise).', 'Tiago Nogueira', 'mapasufmg@gmail.com', 'MAPAS - Mapping, Analysis,  Prognosis and  Actions for Sustainability',
    'IMPLEMENTED', 'SUBMITTED',
    0.0, 0.0,
    'SECTION_III', 'Belo Horizonte-MG', 'Unknown',
    NULL, NULL,
    'MAPAS Project is an Partnership for Research which develops innovative socio-environmental solutions for the historical occurrence of risky occupations in the railways right-of-way in Brazil.', 'MAPAS Project develops innovative solutions to the occurrence of risky irregular occupations in the railway right-of-way operated by the partner cargo transportation concessionaire. For that, management and territorial occupation solutions are being developed to reduce operational insecurity for people, risks to assets and cargo, improving the use of residual areas in railway domain range and preserving social, environmental and economic values shared by the territory and its actors.', 'The methodology comes from the integration between mapping and territorial data, analysis, development of proposals and elaboration of a Generalizable Territorial Solutions Catalog. A catalog composed by associable parameters, that simulates the constraints of the analyzed area and provide architectural intervention possibilities, which are integrated with the UN Sustainable Development Goals. The partnership''s unserviceable materials and their recycling potential or reuse are also applied.',
    TRUE,
    'IFF21', 'Flávio Agostini, Luciana Bragança, Rejane Magiag Loura, Sarah Dapieve, Tiago Nogueira, Natacha Rena, Ana Isabel de Sá', NULL, NULL
);

