    'IMPLEMENTED', 'SUBMITTED',
    0.0, 0.0,
    'SECTION_IV', 'Shanghai', 'China',
    NULL, NULL,
    'People''s Square Metro Station is a political, cultural, tourist and transport hub in the centre of the city of Shanghai, with three interchange lines, a huge flow of people and many public spaces.', 'As one of the busiest metro stations in the centre of Shanghai, People''s Square Station has undergone historical changes and renewal. The station is surrounded by many public and cultural buildings, commercial offices, tourism and leisure resources. The extended underground space with numerous entrances and exits organises huge crowds and meets the activities and lives of people of all ages in a three-dimensional space. People''s Square still has space and opportunities for future development.', 'People''s Square is the result of the people''s struggle for fairness and justice. With the construction of the metro, more and more people were able to reach it and enjoy the central public space of the city, reducing inequalities. Meanwhile, People''s Square Station has undergone several renovations and renewals. Public transport is brought together, cultural buildings are diverse and event facilities are abundant, promoting the sustainability of the city and the community.',
    TRUE,
    'IFF23', 'Shanghai Lab, Tongji University', NULL, NULL
);

-- Row 107: IFF26
INSERT INTO projects (
    organization_name, contact_person, contact_email, project_name,
    project_status, workflow_status,
    funding_needed, funding_spent,
    uia_region, city, country,
    latitude, longitude,
    brief_description, detailed_description, success_factors,
    gdpr_consent,
    external_code, authors, size_sqm, year_completed
) VALUES (
    'Mercia Andrade Viana Dutra', 'Mercia Andrade Viana Dutra', 'mavddias@gmail.com', 'Your Kind Home',
    'IMPLEMENTED', 'SUBMITTED',
    0.0, 0.0,
    'SECTION_III', 'Natal', 'Brazil',
    NULL, NULL,
    'A place can make you happy;
A place can make you emotional;
A place can give you peace;
A place can heal;
A place can enhance wellbeing;
Your place can do all that.

Improve the quality of your life through your spaces. Your home, your workspace, your educational space, your healing space. And make life-long and significant changes.

“Your Kind Home” is an online school where specialized professionals work with consulting and classes to assess important needs in people''s everyday built environments. Making the space less toxic and more friendly to the users and the environment, a healthier and happier place. By being an online school, people from all over the world can be reached and helped.

The classes are meant to include all people, especially those who do not have easy access to specialized professionals like designers and architects. A specific focus on those at risk of exclusion, persons with disabilities, with illness, the needs of children and the elderly. The students, from their own home can begin to promote well-being and start building healthy and prosperous societies step by step.
Classes and consultancies can range from improving hygiene, improving indoor air quality, sick building syndrome, how to have a better layout for a good indoor flow. Learn more about important health factors in a building, for example light, acoustics, air quality, and toxins from buildings and environments.

The healthiest and best place we have is our home. 
We are all connected in the same energy, from inside to outside, from our environment to our mind, all relationships are connected. To bring them together, respect each one of them and balance them in our lives is key for healthy relationships and a healthy environment. 
A healthy being is connected to a healthy space, to a healthy environment.', '“Your Kind Home” is an online school where specialized professionals work with consulting and classes to assess important needs in people''s everyday built environments. Making the space less toxic and more friendly to the users and the environment, a healthier and happier place. By being an online school, people from all over the world can be reached and helped.

The classes are meant to include all people, especially those who do not have easy access to specialized professionals like designers and architects. A specific focus on those at risk of exclusion, persons with disabilities, with illness, the needs of children and the elderly. The students, from their own home can begin to promote well-being and start building healthy and prosperous societies step by step.
Classes and consultancies can range from improving hygiene, improving indoor air quality, sick building syndrome, how to have a better layout for a good indoor flow. Learn more about important health factors in a building, for example light, acoustics, air quality, and toxins from buildings and environments.

The “Kind Architecture” Concept is to create a balance among: 
The Universal Home – Our natural environment and all living things; 
The Inner Home – Your true person;
And The Kind Home – Our best built environment.
A balance that will work as a partnership.

When we educate, we create and invest in not only our future, but the community’s as well. Acting directly with the end users we interact and promote a more sustainable future and we can reach each person and their built environments, but also their connections, a “drop in the ocean” partnership. The private sector and civil society having a shared vision and values, working together for a more sustainable future. From local to global, working and learning together.', 'The “Kind Architecture” Concept is to create a balance among: 
The Universal Home – Our natural environment and all living things; 
The Inner Home – Your true person;
And The Kind Home – Our best built environment.
A balance that will work as a partnership.


We are the link between the discoveries in architecture and living in built environments and the end users. We communicate the benefits in the social, environmental and health that come with a better built environment. Architects and designers will be able to contribute by sharing knowledge, collaborating with other specialized professionals to promote in people''s everyday home more sustainable solutions.


Improve aspects related to comfort, health and well-being of a home through design, classes, consults and coaching, and encourage the involvement of civil society in the efficient use of natural resources, circular economy and social responsibility. 
The end users will be more conscious of their choices, from what to look for when buying bed sheets to a future home. Students will learn about their climate, culture and resources and share what they have learned with others. What will make them happier, what will bring them a healthier lifestyle?


When we educate, we create and invest in not only our future, but the community’s as well. Acting directly with the end users we interact and promote a more sustainable future and we can reach each person and their built environments, but also their connections, a “drop in the ocean” partnership. The private sector and civil society having a shared vision and values, working together for a more sustainable future. From local to global, working and learning together.',
    TRUE,
    'IFF26', 'Mercia Andrade Viana Dutra', NULL, NULL
);

-- Row 108: IFF27
INSERT INTO projects (
    organization_name, contact_person, contact_email, project_name,
    project_status, workflow_status,
    funding_needed, funding_spent,
    uia_region, city, country,
    latitude, longitude,
