) VALUES (
    'College of Architecture and Urban Planning,Tongji University, Shanghai, P.R.CHINA', 'GAO Chen', 'Kroniermillar@163.com', 'Longyang Rd Metro Station - New Forms of Giant Urban Centre',
    'IMPLEMENTED', 'SUBMITTED',
    0.0, 0.0,
    'SECTION_IV', 'Shanghai', 'China',
    NULL, NULL,
    'Longyang Road Station is the terminal station of Phase 1 of Line 2, located in the south of Huamu District and west of Zhangjiang District in Pudong, Shanghai. Adjacent to the elevated road in the inner ring of Pudong, it is built next to Longyang Road. This site has undergone nearly 20 years of construction and additions since the opening of Line 2 in 1997. It has five rail transit lines 2, 7, 16, 18 and Maglev Line, becoming the first station which can transfer 5 lines in the country. Its unique situation may deserve a better mode for city neighborhood.', 'Its radiation range is quite strong, basically covering 50% of the important areas in Shanghai. It is conceivable how terrifying the number of transfers here is during the peak period. The number of passengers can reach about 700,000. Such a large-scale flow of people also brings new potential to the local business and life.
In the future planning, with the completion of the southern TOD project, the airport connection line will pass through the TOD and connect with the station hall of Line 18. Longyang Road will become the first six-line transfer station in the country, and Longyang Road will be Provide living space for citizens with a more open attitude to the city.', 'Part of the space on the first floor is opened to reintegrate the communication between the urban level and the rail transit building.
Open the transfer circulation channel to the outside and combine the business forms on the other side of the road, implant more diversified living spaces in the circulation system, and provide a new way of life for the surrounding people.
Improving the organization of entrances and exits on the first floor of Longyang Plaza, and adding maglev entrances and exits in the transfer passage, forming a new transfer corridor can promote the hub to be more humanized.',
    TRUE,
    'IFF28', 'Shanghai Lab, Tongji University', NULL, NULL
);

