    NULL, NULL,
    'Caoyang Road Station, located in Putuo District, Shanghai, China, is an interchange station for  Line 3, Line 4, Line 11 and  Line 14. Among them, Line 3 and Line 4 are overlapping；Line 14 is interchanged with Line 3, Line 4 and Line 11 in the form of outbound interchange；Line 11 is an intra-station transfer.This is a study within a radius of 200M with Cao Yang Road subway station as the center to analyze the impact of the subway station on urban space and urban life.', 'Since its construction in the 1950s, micro, small and medium-sized enterprises have been encouraged to formalize and grow through access to financial services in order to meet the basic needs of the working class. It continues to this day.
Rich in functions and taking into account the consumption capacity of different groups, it can meet the needs of the general public and the disadvantaged groups - health care, education, social security, etc.
The transportation system is progressively improved, public transportation is easily accessible, public spaces are considered for use by vulnerable people  and at the same time are inclusive so that all people can enjoy safe, green urban spaces.', 'Since its construction in the 1950s, micro, small and medium-sized enterprises have been encouraged to formalize and grow through access to financial services in order to meet the basic needs of the working class. It continues to this day
Rich in functions and taking into account the consumption capacity of different groups, it can meet the needs of the general public and the disadvantaged groups - health care, education, social security, etc.
The transportation system is progressively improved, public transportation is easily accessible, public spaces are considered for use by vulnerable people  and at the same time are inclusive so that all people can enjoy safe, green urban spaces.',
