    'Elisabete França, Maria Teresa Fedeli, Vanessa Padiá, Giovanna Goulart, Ariany Gomes.', 'Debora Tellini Carpentieri', 'deboratellini@gmail.com', 'Jardim da União',
    'IMPLEMENTED', 'SUBMITTED',
    0.0, 0.0,
    'SECTION_III', 'São Paulo - Brazil', 'Unknown',
    NULL, NULL,
    'Urbanization of Jardim da União', 'Jardim da União is a needy community in the southern region of São Paulo city. Originating from irregular occupation, after many challenges, it has been urbanized and soon will receive the property titles from the public authorities, transforming the lives of around 1,538 inhabitants.
Urbanization led to infrastructure eliminating environmental damage. And in partnership with the community, public spaces were designed to be part of the social development and unity of all.', 'The urban project developed in Jardim União sought harmony and balance among housing, environment and social development. Families benefited from the offer of infrastructure and community spaces for sports, leisure, culture and planting, which were used by all residents through different age groups. Several collective events are held, transforming the community through new life opportunities and experiences.',
    TRUE,
    'LDP51', 'Debora Tellini Carpentieri', NULL, NULL
